ks like a children’s book I wanted the story to be something that resonated with adults as well. The page layout and design were heavily influenced by William Blake and William Morris, evoking a sense of illuminated manuscripts and traditional fairytales. Where I felt it appropriate I playfully dispensed with the strict layout and allowed the elements to break out into the margins.</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Illustration: Coralie Bickford-Smith/Penguin</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"4084251d6eb506565e4c60824e558bcda956b58c\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/4084251d6eb506565e4c60824e558bcda956b58c/0_0_4182_2953/1000.jpg\" alt=\"Fox and the star 2\" width=\"1000\" height=\"706\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">This spread is my most blatant homage to William Blake. I wanted to encapsulate his poem Eternity in a single spread.</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Illustration: Coralie Bickford-Smith/Penguin</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"8ac8e57253fbae29115e7fcd21513f18bf0658ba\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/8ac8e57253fbae29115e7fcd21513f18bf0658ba/0_0_4182_2953/1000.jpg\" alt=\"The fox and the star black leaves\" width=\"1000\" height=\"706\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">I really enjoyed playing with the idea of colour. The book itself is comprised of five pantones (this is the name for standardised colours used in printing) and they are used sparingly and with intent. When Fox is no longer with Star the forest turns into a gloomy, dark place.</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Illustration: Coralie Bickford-Smith/Penguin</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"b57d3ed1fd841de3cef66684dbf9700163481c4a\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/b57d3ed1fd841de3cef66684dbf9700163481c4a/0_0_4182_2953/1000.jpg\" alt=\"The fox and the star bugs\" width=\"1000\" height=\"706\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">The forest of the book is teeming with life, although Fox feels isolated and alone on his journey. I wanted to create a story that, consciously or not, the reader could relate to their own experiences.</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Illustration: Coralie Bickford-Smith/Penguin</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"2aa702f56403660e946c5fbcac35e8d3fe0670f6\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/2aa702f56403660e946c5fbcac35e8d3fe0670f6/0_0_4182_2953/1000.jpg\" alt=\"The fox and the star orange fox\" width=\"1000\" height=\"706\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">In fables, foxes are characterised as cunning and calculating creatures. My Fox was none of these. He is a naive innocent soul who is finding his place in the world.</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Illustration: Coralie Bickford-Smith/Penguin</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"f1c951403ea4a9968469e000ef9d85ea0f8f89eb\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/f1c951403ea4a9968469e000ef9d85ea0f8f89eb/0_0_2061_3049/676.jpg\" alt=\"The Fox and The Star\" width=\"676\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">The Fox and the Star by Coralie Bickford-Smith is <a href=\"https://bookshop.theguardian.com/catalog/product/view/id/316571/s/the-fox-and-the-star/\">available from the Guardian bookshop</a>.</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Illustration: Coralie Bickford-Smith/Penguin</span> </figcaption> </figure>","productionOffice":"UK","hasStoryPackage":"false","trailText":"Coralie Bickford-Smith tells us how she made The Fox and the Star, her debut children’s book that has just been crowned Waterstones Book of the Year 2015Check out the G