humbnail\" data-media-id=\"d6f742f453e4153e6186b4eba7ba5e1fbe7086d6\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/11/11/1447262793638/142af9c4-cc5e-44a1-8383-8c9575038d8e-284x420.jpeg\" alt=\"Ellie Marney\" width=\"284\" height=\"420\" class=\"gu-image\" /> </figure>  <p>That being said, the majority of the novel was built around the investigation that they embark on. This was actually really fascinating especially when they were discussing the forensics of the murder and the inferences they could make from it. This was where the novel was at its strongest, as it was generally fast paced and explored Mycroft and Watts’ relationship both in solving cases and as friends. </p> <p>The twists in the story were well executed and unexpected, reminiscent of Arthur Conan Doyle himself. Overall this novel was enjoyable to read but its narrator weighed the story down and prevented it from having more of an effect on the reader.</p> <aside class=\"element element-rich-link element--thumbnail\"> <p> <span>Related: </span><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">How do I get involved in the Guardian children's books site?</a> </p> </aside>  <ul> <li><strong>Buy this book at the <a href=\"https://bookshop.theguardian.com/every-breath-266549.html\">Guardian Bookshop</a></strong></li> </ul> <h2><strong>Want to tell the world about a book you’ve read? <a href=\"http://preview.gutools.co.uk/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">Join the site</a> and send us your review!</strong></h2>","productionOffice":"UK","hasStoryPackage":"false","trailText":"<strong>Awkward unicorn:</strong> ‘What starts out as an innocent investigation into the death of a friend begins to turn into something much more dangerous’","headline":"Every Breath by Ellie Marney - review","byline":"Awkward unicorn","commentable":"false","standfirst":"<p>‘What starts ou